11)\u003c/pre\u003e\u003cb\u003eIn a Jupyter environment, please rerun this cell to show the HTML representation or trust the notebook. \u003cbr /\u003eOn GitHub, the HTML representation is unable to render, please try loading this page with nbviewer.org.\u003c/b\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv class=\\\"sk-container\\\" hidden\u003e\u003cdiv class=\\\"sk-item\\\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\\\"sk-estimator fitted sk-toggleable\\\"\u003e\u003cinput class=\\\"sk-toggleable__control sk-hidden--visually\\\" id=\\\"sk-estimator-id-1\\\" type=\\\"checkbox\\\" checked\u003e\u003clabel for=\\\"sk-estimator-id-1\\\" class=\\\"sk-toggleable__label fitted sk-toggleable__label-arrow\\\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cdiv\u003eKNeighborsClassifier\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003ca class=\\\"sk-estimator-doc-link fitted\\\" rel=\\\"noreferrer\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" href=\\\"https://scikit-learn.org/1.6/modules/generated/sklearn.neighbors.KNeighborsClassifier.html\\\"\u003e?\u003cspan\u003eDocumentation for KNeighborsClassifier\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan class=\\\"sk-estimator-doc-link fitted\\\"\u003ei\u003cspan\u003eFitted\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/label\u003e\u003cdiv class=\\\"sk-toggleable__content fitted\\\"\u003e\u003cpre\u003eKNeighborsClassifier(metric=\u0026#x27;euclidean\u0026#x27;, n_neighbors=11)\u003c/pre\u003e\u003c/div\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\"","      ],","      \"text/plain\": [","       \"KNeighborsClassifier(metric='euclidean', n_neighbors=11)\"","      ]","     },","     \"execution_count\": 47,","     \"metadata\": {},","     \"output_type\": \"execute_result\"","    }","   ],","   \"source\": [","    \"knn = KNeighborsClassifier(\\n\",","    \"    n_neighbors=best_k,\\n\",","    \"    metric='euclidean',\\n\",","    \"    weights='uniform')\\n\",","    \"knn.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train)\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"id\": \"37a2e188-16b0-4b9f-97bb-f7045eebed2f\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"* Creates the final KNN model with the best K found above. metric='euclidean' means straight-line distance between points in 30D space. weights='uniform' means all K neighbours get equal voting power. .fit() trains the model on the training data — KNN simply memorizes all training points.\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"id\": \"d282b870-d923-412a-aabb-7838a43ba292\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"## Evaluate Model\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": 48,","   \"id\": \"412de051-0a9d-4149-8e90-041f8dadc555\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"y_pred = knn.predict(X_test_scaled)\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"id\": \"2bb9f59c-9be7-4667-988f-67a96a3e7b5a\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"* Model looks at each test sample, finds its K nearest neighbours from training data, takes a majority vote, and returns prediction (0 or 1).\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": 49,","   \"id\": \"b4eb14d8-5b3c-49fc-8617-af49c71b9bbe\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"y_prob = knn.predict_proba(X_test_scaled)[:, 1]\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"id\": \"6361db5e-50d7-44de-873c-1c9ef12405c6\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"* Instead of just 0 or 1, this gives a probability score between 0 and 1. [:, 1] selects the probability of being Malignant (class 1). Used later for ROC curve.\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": 50,","   \"id\": \"c7fd6406-5dad-46e6-94f8-33c094572c18\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [","    {","     \"data\": {","      \"text/plain\": [","       \"0.9473684210526315\"","      ]","     },","     \"execution_count\": 50,","     \"metadata\": {},","     \"output_type\": \"execute_result\"","    }","   ],","   \"source\": [","    \"accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"id\": \"acbef181-8851-41ad-9a3e-4dbc2539aa08\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"* Percentage of total predictions that were correct. Formula: (TP + TN) / Total\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": 51,","   \"id\": \"b434ec46-d96c-4223-8db8-5e8209f5085b\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [","    {","     \"data\": {","      \"text/plain\": [","       \"0.9736842105263158\"","      ]","     },","     \"execution_count\": 51,","     \"metadata\": {},","     \"output_type\": \"execute_result\"","    }","   ],","   \"source\": [","    \"precision_score(y_test, y_pred)\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"id\": \"a0966ae3-d445-43b2-b990-a68999275cae\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"* Out of all cases predicted as Malignant, how many actually were Malignant. Formula: TP / (TP + FP). High precision = fewer false alarms.\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": 52,","   \"id\": \"994b90a2-c405-4c79-a800-6c3aa78ff31d\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [","    {","     \"data\": {","      \"text/plain\": [","       \"0.8809523809523809\"","      ]","     },","     \"execution_count\": 52,","     \"metadata\": {},","     \"output_type\": \"execute_result\"","    }","   ],","   \"source\": [","    \"recall_score(y_test, y_pred)\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"id\": \"8e17be37-a497-4155-a0d1-5904dad1fc7d\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"* Out of all actual Malignant cases, how many did the model correctly catch. Formula: TP / (TP + FN). High recall = fewer missed cancers. In medical diagnosis, recall is more critical than precision.\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": 53,","   \"id\": \"cbe55af3-846c-479d-8ff9-da2426f8c001\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [","    {","     \"data\": {","      \"text/plain\": [","       \"0.925\"","      ]","     },","     \"execution_count\": 53,","     \"metadata\": {},","     \"output_type\": \"execute_result\"","    }","   ],","   \"source\": [","    \"f1_score(y_test, y_pred)\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"id\": \"c0c5503c-c78a-4d5a-a424-cab97d94d3f7\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"* Harmonic mean of precision and recall. Gives a single balanced score when both matter. Formula: 2 * (Precision * Recall) / (Precision + Recall)\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": 54,","   \"id\": \"4f344dae-3570-4947-82ad-698a928a3885\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [","    {","     \"data\": {","      \"text/plain\": [","       \"'              precision    recall  f1-score   support\\\\n\\\\n           0       0.93      0.99      0.96        72\\\\n           1       0.97      0.88      0.93        42\\\\n\\\\n    accuracy                           0.95       114\\\\n   macro avg       0.95      0.93      0.94       114\\\\nweighted avg       0.95      0.95      0.95       114\\\\n'\"","      ]","     },","     \"execution_count\": 54,","     \"metadata\": {},","     \"output_type\": \"execute_result\"","    }","   ],","   \"source\": [","    \"classification_report(y_test, y_pred)\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"id\": \"7c34234d-e959-4c2f-b592-df371a8ab353\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"* Prints a full table showing precision, recall, F1, and support (sample count) for both classes — Benign and Malignant — together.\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"id\": \"ad6b25a8-6949-43ad-bb80-d8318c1f4a75\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"### Confusion Matrix\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": 55,","   \"id\": \"2b03ac27-81b0-4937-9c0c-53af3bae1694\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [","    {","     \"data\": {","      \"text/plain\": [","       \"\u003cAxes: \u003e\"","      ]","     },","     \"execution_count\": 55,","     \"metadata\": {},","     \"output_type\": \"execute_result\"","    },","    {","     \"data\": {","      \"image/png\": \"\",","      \"text/plain\": [","       \"\u003cFigure size 640x480 with 2 Axes\u003e\"","      ]","     },","     \"metadata\": {},","     \"output_type\": \"display_data\"","    }","   ],","   \"source\": [","    \"cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)\\n\",","    \"sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues')\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"id\": \"72d7d7ce-19d3-4dea-a4c0-509a97927c00\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"* Creates a 2x2 matrix showing 4 types of results. annot=True prints the numbers inside each box. fmt='d' means display as integer.\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": 56,","   \"id\": \"578a8d6f-1496-4260-bb74-20544aa34371\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"tn, fp, fn, tp = cm.ravel()\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"id\": \"d9ea6218-28ed-41cb-aa0c-9c5329230252\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"* Unpacks the 4 values from confusion matrix. TP = correctly predicted Malignant. TN = correctly predicted Benign. FP = Benign predicted as Malignant (false alarm). FN = Malignant predicted as Benign (most dangerous mistake in cancer detection).\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"id\": \"4d8d11df-64b9-4925-a40f-9d3fab9b65fa\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"### ROC Curve\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": 57,","   \"id\": \"b54e456b-0921-4eeb-896c-f4bd93d4e6cd\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_test, y_prob)\\n\",","    \"roc_auc = auc(fpr, tpr)\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"id\": \"22da5171-bdaf-43a4-ba98-55a5ae81c99c\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"* ROC curve plots True Positive Rate vs False Positive Rate at different decision thresholds. AUC (Area Under Curve) summarizes the whole curve in one number. AUC = 1.0 is perfect, AUC = 0.5 is random guessing. Our model should get ~0.97–0.99.\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": null,","   \"id\": \"d0ca86e9-d873-430a-90f3-12447944dbcf\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], linestyle='--')\\n\",","    \"plt.show()\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"id\": \"ee4dcb38-dfe0-472f-b478-ffbe94d7ae0b\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"* This dashed diagonal line represents a random classifier (AUC = 0.5). Our model's curve should be far above this line — the further above, the better.\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": 58,","   \"id\": \"9efc1a0d-d57e-44a3-9629-2b47329649f0\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [","    {","     \"data\": {","      \"text/html\": [","       \"\u003cstyle\u003e#sk-container-id-2 {\\n\",","       \"  /* Definition of color scheme common for light and dark mode */\\n\",","       \"  --sklearn-color-text: #000;\\n\",","       \"  --sklearn-color-text-muted: #666;\\n\",","       \"  --sklearn-color-line: gray;\\n\",","       \"  /* Definition of color scheme for unfitted estimators */\\n\",","       \"  --sklearn-color-unfitted-level-0: #fff5e6;\\n\",","       \"  --sklearn-color-unfitted-level-1: #f6e4d2;\\n\",","       \"  --sklearn-color-unfitted-level-2: #ffe0b3;\\n\",","       \"  --sklearn-color-unfitted-level-3: chocolate;\